![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2025/12/20251126_rockland-bus_2.jpg?w=1200)

The intersection of Broadway and Eliza Steele Drive in Rockland where 12-year-old Brayden Callahan was struck and killed by a school bus on Nov. 21. . (Gregory Rec/Staff Photographer)

The Camden man who was driving the school bus that hit and killed a 12-year-old Rockland student has been arrested and charged with manslaughter, police say.

Jeffery Colburn, 65, was arrested on Thursday after he was indicted by a grand jury and a warrant for his arrest was issued by the Knox County District Attorney’s Office, Rockland police said in a news release.

Brayden Callahan, 12, of Rockland, died after he was [hit by a school bus on Nov. 21](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/11/24/rockland-school-district-cancels-classes-following-student-death/) at the intersection of Broadway and Eliza Steele Drive, police said.

