The boy was crossing in front of the bus in a crosswalk when Colburn accelerated and ran him over, the crash report said. It indicated that Colburn did not keep his eyes on the road after dropping the student off.

Brayden was flown by a LifeFlight helicopter to Maine Medical Center, but ultimately died due to his injuries, police said. It was the first of [two school bus-related deaths in Maine](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/12/17/parents-heartbroken-after-2-maine-students-killed-by-school-buses-in-a-month/) late last year.

Colburn was subsequently placed on administrative leave, and by December [was no longer working for the district](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/12/04/bus-driver-in-fatal-rockland-crash-no-longer-works-for-district/).

